      "cooked": "<p>Hi! One thing I am missing from competitors is some kind of insight into what workouts my friends are riding, as an alternative to Strava.</p>\n<p>All that I do on Strava is check other peoples indoor cycling workouts and it would be nice to do this in app. Maybe just a simple \u201eable to follow someone, they can accept the request, now I see their posts in my activity feed\u201c. Or that i can go to their profile and activity feed.</p>\n<p>I\u2018ve thought about building a web app for this myself but this would then be <a href=\"https://xkcd.com/927/\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">this xkcd</a> <img src=\"https://forums.trainerday.com/images/emoji/twitter/smiley.png?v=12\" title=\":smiley:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":smiley:\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\"></p>",
